  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d4825.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d4825.gif" alt="overlaid" border="0" height="108" /></a>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d3280.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d3280.gif" alt="overlaid" border="0" height="108" /></a>
  <br />
  <em>
  Flag of <a href="es-b-sal.html">Sant Andreu de Llavaneres</a>, Spain (fotw); 
  Flag of <a href="rs-stpaz.html">Stara Pazova</a>, Serbia (fotw);
  Flag of <a href="br-pb107.html">Lucena</a>, 
  Brazil (fotw) </em></dd>

  <hr /><a name="ownerabsentflag"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">OWNER ABSENT FLAG</dt>
  <dd>In US usage the practice, almost certainly obsolete, of flying a plain blue flag 
  from the starboard yardarm (or spreader) of a pleasure vessel when the owner is absent &ndash; 
  an absence pennant (see also 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvd2.html#dinnerflag">dinner flag</a>&rsquo;, 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvg6.html#guestflag">guest on board flag</a>&rsquo;, 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvm2.html#mealpennant">meal pennant</a>&rsquo; and 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dv-y.html#yardarm">yardarm</a>&rsquo;).
  <p>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d540.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d540.gif" alt="owner absent" border="0" height="108" /></a>
  <br />
  <a href="xf~yct.html#ownerabs"><em>Owner Absent Flag</em></a><em>, US (fotw)</em></dd>
